      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Royal Geographical Society of Australasia ¶ Nov 6 1890 ¶ J. Duncan Esqr ¶ Wellington ¶ My dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M90.11.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Arthur Vogan to J. Duncan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Folder 1, box 84, Hector papers, Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa Archives, Wellington.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Royal Geographical Society of Australasia</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Nov 6 1890</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">J. Duncan Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Wellington</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust you will forgive the liberty I take in asking you to do me the following service:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Thomas Elder has placed a large sum of money, for the purposes of Exploratory Work in Central Australia,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Elder Scientific Exploring Expedition, 1891-2.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> in the hands of Baron Sir Ferd. Von Müeller K.C.B.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M’s British knighthood was K.C.M.G., not K.C.B.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> FRS &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am desirous of joining the party; but it will need all the influence I can bring to bear to obtain me a place on staff as there are so many good men applying.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>See M to E. Ramsay, 11 November 1890.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was the sole representative of N. Zealand on the R.G.S.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Geographical Society.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> of Australasia's New Guinea expedition of 1885; and I want you to get me a letter to Baron Von Mueller from the Premier, or Dr Hector, or Dr Buller, asking a place for me as a N.Z. representative as well as for my past services in this line. I was artist on the expedition mentioned above; and discovered the Einsleigh river<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Einasleigh River, Qld.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> thermal springs — the only terraced springs yet known in Australia — in 1888 (and am credited with this &amp; other geological discovery in Professors Jack's (Queenld Gov. Geologist) and Etheridge's (N.S.W. Gov Pathologist<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Palaeontologist.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>) new book on Australia,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Jack &amp; Etheridge (1892), p. 626.</p>
               </note> which I have assisted to illustrate.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There are no illustrations in vol. 1. In vol. 2, none of the 44 palaeontological plates are signed by Vogan; plates 45–58 are geological sections, none of which are signed; plate 59, a plan of the Charters Towers Goldfields, credits the engraver but not the delineator; <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the plates 60-68 are microscopic petrographical sections, none drawn by Vogan. Artists involved in the Geological Map are not identified, the credit being 'Drawn and lithographed at the Surveyor General's office'. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Last year I made a geological report for the R.G.S. of A on 1000 miles of new country in N. W. Queensland, in the vicinity of the Herbert river, lat. 21°S.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Not identified.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Any assistance you can render me in this way will be gratefully remembered.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I may mention that Sir George Grey has kindly given me an introductory letter to Sr T. Elder pressing my claims;<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At about the same time as he wrote the present letter, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vogan wrote again to Grey, explaining that he had learned that Elder was in England and that all matters concerning the expedition had been placed in M's hands, and asking Grey now to write to M, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'with whom (members of our Society here give me to believe) you are intimately acquainted', in support of his candidature (A. Vogan to G. Grey, H18(5), Grey papers, Auckland Central City Library).</p>
               </note> I am also backed up by Dr Ramsay, Curator Australian Museum, Harrie Wood, Asst Secty Mines NSW; Maiden, Curator of Techl<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Technological.</p>
               </note> Museum &amp;c as well as our branch of Society.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust Mrs Duncan &amp; yourself are well — I hear your sons are doing well — and that Miss Duncan has enjoyed her trip to England. It may interest you to know that I have a book coming out in London in Jany.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vogan (1891).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With kd regards to Mrs Duncan &amp; yourself,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ever yours regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Arthur J Vogan</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. As a well-known Journalist the Premier may be enclined to help me.<note xml:id="ftn13" type="footnote" n="13">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>No supporting letter to M from Harry Atkinson, then in his fourth term (1887-91) as Premier of New Zealand, has been found. Vogan was not a member of the exploration party; see Lindsay (1893), p. 15, for a list of members and their roles. The medical officer was also the photographer, but no artist was included. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
